
-> Please use the syntax to create EKS cluster

  1) eksctl create cluster --name=< name > --region=us-east-1 --zones=us-east-1a,us-east-1b --without-nodegroup

-> Once the cluster is created associate IAM OIDC Provider for EKS cluster with Following Command

  2) eksctl utils associate-iam-oidc-provider --region us-east-1 --cluster < clu name> --approve

 > Create  node group

   3) eksctl create nodegroup --cluster= < cluster name > \
                       --region=us-east-1 \
                       --name=< desiredname> \
                       --node-type=t3.medium \
                       --nodes=2 \
                       --nodes-min=2 \
                       --nodes-max=4 \
                       --node-volume-size=20 \
                       --ssh-access \
                       --ssh-public-key=< key-pair> \
                       --managed \
                       --asg-access \
                       --external-dns-access \
                       --full-ecr-access \
                       --appmesh-access \
                       --alb-ingress-access 


